The paper discusses self-aware management and scheduling in the context of cloud applications, which falls under the domain of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the practical characteristics, benefits, and drawbacks of self-awareness approaches, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the importance of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data management (cs.DS) in self-aware cloud and datacenter applications.
